Standard and Poor's Corp said itraised to A-1 from A-2 American Security Corp's commercialpaper.    S and P also upgraded, to A and A-1 from BBB-plus and A-2respectively, the certificates of deposit of AmericanSecurity's lead bank, American Security Bank N.A.    The rating agency said the actions reflected the firm'smerger with what it termed a stronger Maryland National Corp,as well as American's improving performance. S and P said themerger would allow American Security to diversify its wholesalefunding base. Reuter&#3;